Bachelor of Science

The B.Sc. program offers students a comprehensive understanding of scientific principles, theories, and practical applications within their chosen field of study, preparing them for diverse career paths in Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics, Healthcare, Research, etc. Typically, the duration of a B.Sc. program is 3 years.

{/* First Year */}

First Year B.Sc (F.Y.B.Sc)

Semester I

  • Chemistry (Basics in Physics, Inorganic and Organic Chemistry-I)
  • Physics (Introduction to Mechanics)
  • Mathematics (Algebra-I and Calculus-I)
  • Calibration of Glassware and Instruments-I
  • Basic Statistical Tools in Chemistry-I
  • Indian Constitution
  • Communication Skills in English
  • Indian Knowledge System

Semester II

  • Basics in Physical, Inorganic and Organic Chemistry-II
  • Chemistry Practical-II
  • Discrete Mathematics and Calculus-II
  • Mathematics Practical-II
  • Optics
  • Physics Practical-II
  • Commercial Analysis of Food Samples
  • Data Analysis in Chemistry
  • Heritage Sites in India
  • लेखन कौशल्य - १ कार्यालयीन लेखन व्यवहार व पत्रव्यवहार
  • Introduction to Cultural Activities
{/* Second Year */}

Second Year B.Sc (S.Y.B.Sc)

Semester III

  • Foundation Course - Contemporary Issues - III
  • To be updated...

Semester IV

  • Physics Paper-I
  • Physics Paper-II
  • Physics Paper-III
  • Physics Practical
  • Chemistry Paper-I
  • Chemistry Paper-II
  • Chemistry Paper-III
  • Chemistry Practical
  • Foundation Course-IV
{/* Third Year */}

Third Year B.Sc (T.Y.B.Sc)

Semester V

  • Chemistry - Analytical Chemistry
  • Chemistry - Inorganic Chemistry
  • Chemistry - Organic Chemistry
  • Chemistry - Physical Chemistry
  • Elective/Specialization Paper (e.g. Environmental Chemistry, Medicinal Chemistry)

Semester VI

  • Chemistry - Analytical Chemistry
  • Chemistry - Inorganic Chemistry
  • Chemistry - Organic Chemistry
  • Chemistry - Physical Chemistry
  • Drugs and Dyes
